    "In Sports, respiration was used to measure the level of physical arousal and fatigue during exergames (e.g., Charoensook et al. 2019), and in Education and Training, it was helpful to know if users can control their physiological parameters in different situations (e.g., Michela et al. 2022).",
    "Eye tracking, shown in light blue, was measured in most areas (5.1%).",
    "More widespread usage was expected, due to the built-in eye tracking systems that can now be found in some HMDs.",
